dc_description_s: Cartographic Details: Scale approximately 1:2,200,000. Relief shown by hachures. Originally folded to 21 x 15 cm. Includes 4 insets: The Malay Peninsula &c. showing British possessions beyond the Ganges -- Distances and bearings from Bombay -- Distances and bearings from Madras -- Distances and bearings from Calcutta.|84 x 130 centimeters|Scale approximately 1:2,200,000|Ames Library of South Asia Maps
